Class Variable

  • java.lang.Object
    • Argument
      • Variable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.Comparator
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MathVariable

    public class Variable
extends Argument
    This class defines a variable in Prolog syntax. Its name (by convention) must begin with a capitol letter; that convention is NOT enforced. In Example-Generation, information is stored on each variable that constrains the kind of Individual who could be bound to this Variable.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
